<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Idi_Amin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=20" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="references-small references-column-count references-column-count-2" style="-moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-birth_date_place-0">^ <a href="#cite_ref-birth_date_place_0-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-birth_date_place_0-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-birth_date_place_0-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> Many sources, like Encyclopædia Britannica, Encarta and the Columbia Encyclopedia, hold that Amin was born in Koboko or Kampala circa 1925, and that the exact date of his birth is unknown. Researcher Fred Guweddeko claimed that Amin was born on 17 May 1928,<a href="http://www.monitor.co.ug/artman/publish/special_adi-amin-profile/Rejected_then_taken_in_by_dad_a_timeline_2.shtml" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.monitor.co.ug/artman/publish/special_adi-amin-profile/Rejected_then_taken_in_by_dad_a_timeline_2.shtml" rel="nofollow">[1]</a>, but that is disputed.<a href="http://www.mail-archive.com/ugandanet@kym.net/msg06472.html" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.mail-archive.com/ugandanet@kym.net/msg06472.html" rel="nofollow">[2]</a> The only certainty is that Amin was born some time during the mid-1920s.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Ullman1978-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Ullman1978_1-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFUllman1978">Ullman, Richard H. (April 1978), "<a href="http://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/29141/richard-h-ullman/human-rights-and-economic-power-the-united-states-versus-idi-ami" class="external text" title="http://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/29141/richard-h-ullman/human-rights-and-economic-power-the-united-states-versus-idi-ami" rel="nofollow">Human Rights and Economic Power: The United States Versus Idi Amin</a>", <i><a href="/wiki/Foreign_Affairs_(journal)" title="Foreign Affairs (journal)" class="mw-redirect">Foreign Affairs</a></i><span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/29141/richard-h-ullman/human-rights-and-economic-power-the-united-states-versus-idi-ami" class="external free" title="http://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/29141/richard-h-ullman/human-rights-and-economic-power-the-united-states-versus-idi-ami" rel="nofollow">http://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/29141/richard-h-ullman/human-rights-and-economic-power-the-united-states-versus-idi-ami</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved on 2009-03-26</span>,  "The most conservative estimates by informed observers hold that President Idi Amin Dada and the terror squads operating under his loose direction have killed 100,000 Ugandans in the seven years he has held power."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Human+Rights+and+Economic+Power%3A+The+United+States+Versus+Idi+Amin&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BForeign+Affairs+%28journal%29%7CForeign+Affairs%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Ullman&amp;rft.aufirst=Richard+H.&amp;rft.au=Ullman%2C+Richard+H.&amp;rft.date=April+1978&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreignaffairs.com%2Farticles%2F29141%2Frichard-h-ullman%2Fhuman-rights-and-economic-power-the-united-states-versus-idi-ami&amp;rf